It is a process of identifying ,cleaning,transforming and modeling the  data to discover the meaningful and useful information




	• To analyze the data core components of analytics are divided into following categories


		• Descriptive
		• Diagnostic
		• Predictive
		• Prescriptive
		• Artificial Intelligence (AI)


	1. DESCRIPTIVE : (what happened)
	

	• By developing KPI (Key performance Indicators) we can analyze the failure and success rate 
	
	2. DIAGNOSTIC : (Why events happened)
	
	• They find from the descriptive analytics to discover the cause of events
	• Then KPI where investigated to know about why this gets better and became worse 
	
	THREE STEPS :
	
		1.   Identify the anamolis of the data ,this might be unexpected changes in metrics (or) particular market
		2.   Collect data relate to anamolis
		3. Use statistical techniques to discover relationships and trends that explain anamolis
		
	3. PREDICTIVE ANALYSIS : (What will happen)
	
	• Give analysis which might happen in future .
	• It helps to historical data to identify trends and determine if they're likely to occur 
	
	4.  PRESCRIPTIVE ANALYSIS : (What action should we take  to achieve the target or goal)

	• By taking this analysis,will take data driven descision 
	• This rely on machine learning as one of the strategies to find patterns in large semantic models
	
    5.     ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE (AI) : 

	• In context of analytics , AI enables systems to process vast amount of data ,recognize patterns and deliver insights with minimal human intervention
	
	
	

	
	
		
		
